<item>
            <title>[LU-2605] reduce the failover time when the MDS and OSS are on the same machine in High Availability</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2605</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In case of failure of the 1st server, the MDS1 and the OSS1 will fail in the same time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then the failover on the 2nd node will wait 5 more minutes because the moved OST will wait the timeout for the failed client MDS1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This case of 2 servers with failover and 2 active OSS is important for little configurations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(BULL)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Linux, 2 physical servers,&lt;br/&gt;
the 1st holds the active MDS and an active OSS and the 2nd holds the passive MDS and an active OSS</environment>
